  "prompt": "Can Indians work for NASA?",
  "response": "Yes, Indians can work for NASA. In fact, many Indian and Indian-American scientists and engineers have worked at NASA in various capacities. NASA actively recruits talented individuals from diverse backgrounds, and nationality is not a barrier to employment. However, there are some considerations:\n\n1. U.S. Citizenship: Most NASA positions require U.S. citizenship due to the sensitive nature of some projects.\n\n2. Visa and Work Permits: Non-U.S. citizens may be able to work at NASA through specific visa programs or as contractors.\n\n3. Notable Indian NASA Employees: Some prominent examples include:\n- Dr. Kalpana Chawla (first Indian-born woman in space)\n- Dr. Sunita Williams (astronaut)\n- Dr. Pramod Kale (engineer)\n- Many scientists and researchers of Indian origin\n\n4. Requirements: Candidates must meet NASA's educational, professional, and technical qualifications.\n\n5. Indian Space Research Organization (ISRO) Collaboration: NASA and ISRO also have collaborative research and space exploration programs.\n\nSo while U.S. citizenship is typically required for most positions, Indians can and do work at NASA through various pathways.",
